http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Visakhapatnam/Students-collect-blankets-for-poor/article13980591.ece

Members of Interact Club of Sri Prakash Vidyaniketan collected over 1,000 blankets for poor children and 100 of them were distributed to needy children on Sunday.Chairman of Visakhapatnam Cooperative Bank Ch. Raghavendra Rao, CPI State assistant secretary J.V. Satyanarayana Murthy and Deputy Director of Rajbhat University of Bangkok Janchai Ying Prayoon gave away blankets to the children from lower economic strata at a meeting. The guests appreciated the efforts of the children and encouraged them to participate in such good deeds. They also praised the school administration for making efforts to inculcate such values among the children. School director Chitturi Vasu Prakash congratulated the children on their efforts and motivated them to continue to ‘share and care’.